    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear emphasis on power-speed combinations in favorable matchups. **Kyle Tucker** (76.66) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (75.04) headline our lineup as the strongest plays of the day. Both benefit from excellent situational data: **Kyle Tucker** leverages an elite xwOBA of .372 against Colin Rea, while **Luis Robert Jr.** gains a significant 14% boost from a dynamic platoon advantage against Jose Quintana. **Jackson Merrill** (70.91) also remains a top-tier start despite a 36% rain risk; his projection is buoyed by a strong matchup against Zac Gallen, where he retains a 13% platoon edge and high-leverage order position. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.40) rounds out our elite group, capitalizing on a 7% platoon boost against Joey Cantillo and favorable park factors.\n\nStrategic considerations for today prioritize matchup vulnerability over raw base projections. **Andy Pages** (59.96) and **Miguel Vargas** (59.46) are strong secondary options, with **Andy Pages** receiving a wind-aided boost that pushes his utility higher despite a difficult matchup. Conversely, **Gunnar Henderson** (53.07) represents a more precarious start; while his lineup position is critical, he faces the formidable Garrett Crochet, suffering a 19% penalty due to the pitcher's skill and a 15% hit from a disadvantageous platoon. Regarding bench decisions, **Marcell Ozuna** (47.27) was the closest exclusion; while he carries a respectable base, his score was suppressed by a lower park adjustment and an unfavorable matchup against Jacob Misiorowski, ultimately keeping him on the bench in favor of players with higher ceiling potential today. Managers should monitor the weather in the **Jackson Merrill** game closely, as the 36% rain risk introduces late-breaking volatility to one of our most important outfield assets.",
